Diagnosis
. Antennal scrobes join below frontal suture (
Figs 9, 10
); female flagellomeres short and stout (
Fig. 7
), e.g. 1 
st
flagellomere 2.4× as long as wide; male scape 3.7× as long as wide (
Fig. 8
); forewing speculum open below; scutellum flat with posteromedian part smooth and shiny (
Fig. 12
); propodeum with median carina with sides rounded and converging towards posterior part, and with anterior part blunt (
Figs 12
, 
13
); first gastral tergite with posterior ¾ with punctures. Very similar to 

H. depressus

but differs in having a larger propodeal spiracle (
Fig. 13
), female gaster with apex distinctly more blunt (
Fig. 15
), and entire thoracic dorsum bright metallic bluish-green (
Fig. 6
), with or without purple tinges.
